Welcome to the W3C {{ group.name }}!

You can find essential information about the group on this page:

   https://www.w3.org/groups/{{ type }}/{{ group.shortname }}/

including the calendar of teleconferences (with instructions for
joining),

   https://www.w3.org/groups/{{ type }}/{{ group.shortname }}/calendar/

the list of participants,

   https://www.w3.org/groups/{{ type }}/{{ group.shortname }}/participants/

mailing lists and GitHub repositories,

   https://www.w3.org/groups/{{ type }}/{{ group.shortname }}/tools/

the current and previous charters, how to join or leave the group,
and more.

The W3C's general page about MathML is

   https://www.w3.org/Math/

And this page contains a lot of practical information for members
of W3C groups in general:

   https://www.w3.org/Guide/

If you have not already done so, please, link your GitHub account to
your W3C account:

   https://www.w3.org/users/myprofile/connectedaccounts

All participants are required to follow the W3C Code of Conduct:

   https://www.w3.org/policies/code-of-conduct/

Should you have any questions on how to get up to speed with the
Group, please get in touch with the Staff Contact of the group,
Bert Bos <bert@w3.org>
